Package: HSRC
Type: Package
Title: Useful functions for perioperative research
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Danny J. N. Wong
Maintainer: Danny J. N. Wong <dwong@rcoa.ac.uk>
Description: 
    This is a collection of functions (and eventually data), which R users within the HSRC might find useful. Currently there are only 3 functions for calculating perioperative morbidity and mortality risks, which rely heavily on the package dplyr.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.4.0),
    dplyr (>= 0.7.6)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    tidyverse,
    rlang
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
